---
// Testimonials section featuring reviews written by programming languages.
// Styled in light-theme premium to match the page's theme and the reference layout.
---

<section
  id="testimonials"
  class="w-full py-16 md:py-24 bg-bg-main relative overflow-hidden"
>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
      <h2
        class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-text-primary tracking-tight mb-6 leading-tight"
      >
        The Engineering Knowledge Base That Understands Your <span
          class="text-primary italic">Project Architecture</span
        >.
      </h2>
      <p
        class="text-text-secondary text-base md:text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
      >
        Hear what the programming languages themselves have to say...
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 3-Column Responsive Masonry Layout -->
    <div
      class="relative columns-1 md:columns-2 lg:columns-3 gap-6 [column-fill:_balance]"
    >
      <!-- Card 1: TypeScript -->
      <div class="break-inside-avoid-column mb-6 md:pt-4">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full p-6 bg-white border border-border/30 rounded-xl group min-h-fit shadow-2xs"
        >
          <!-- Body Text (Top 75%) -->
          <p
            class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 font-sans font-normal"
          >
            "Finally, a documentation engine that respects type boundaries. It
            parses my complex unions and AST graphs with total fidelity,
            updating integration guides the moment a type alias changes."
          </p>

          <!-- Author Profile anchored at bottom -->
          <div class="flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-3 pt-2">
            <div
              class="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden"
            >
              <img
                src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/typescript/3178C6"
                alt="TypeScript logo"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2">
              <span class="text-text-primary font-normal text-xs truncate"
                >TypeScript</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2: Python -->
      <div class="break-inside-avoid-column mb-6">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full p-6 bg-white border border-border/30 rounded-xl group min-h-fit shadow-2xs"
        >
          <!-- Body Text (Top 75%) -->
          <p
            class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 font-sans font-normal"
          >
            "The engine accurately tracks how my dynamic data objects mutate
            across complex function blocks, transforming unstable logic into a
            static reference you can actually trust."
          </p>

          <!-- Author Profile anchored at bottom -->
          <div class="flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-3 pt-2">
            <div
              class="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden"
            >
              <img
                src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/python/3776AB"
                alt="Python logo"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2">
              <span class="text-text-primary font-normal text-xs truncate"
                >Python</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3: Go -->
      <div class="break-inside-avoid-column mb-6">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full p-6 bg-white border border-border/30 rounded-xl group min-h-fit shadow-2xs"
        >
          <!-- Body Text (Top 75%) -->
          <p
            class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 font-sans font-normal"
          >
            "I refuse to let massive config files bloat my project roots.
            Penqwin indexes my package boundaries and structs in milliseconds,
            building a system blueprint with zero added boilerplate."
          </p>

          <!-- Author Profile anchored at bottom -->
          <div class="flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-3 pt-2">
            <div
              class="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden"
            >
              <img
                src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/go/00ADD8"
                alt="Go logo"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2">
              <span class="text-text-primary font-normal text-xs truncate"
                >Go</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 4: Rust -->
      <div class="break-inside-avoid-column mb-6">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full p-6 bg-white border border-border/30 rounded-xl group min-h-fit shadow-2xs"
        >
          <!-- Body Text (Top 75%) -->
          <p
            class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 font-sans font-normal"
          >
            "If documentation doesn't match the strict ownership contracts of my
            compiler, it's noise. Wondered by how Penqwin analyzes trait
            boundaries to produce technical manuals as resilient as my
            binaries."
          </p>

          <!-- Author Profile anchored at bottom -->
          <div class="flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-3 pt-2">
            <div
              class="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden"
            >
              <img
                src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/rust/F24E1E"
                alt="Rust logo"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2">
              <span class="text-text-primary font-normal text-xs truncate"
                >Rust</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 5: JavaScript -->
      <div class="break-inside-avoid-column mb-6 md:pt-1">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full p-6 bg-white border border-border/30 rounded-xl group min-h-fit shadow-2xs"
        >
          <!-- Body Text (Top 75%) -->
          <p
            class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 font-sans font-normal"
          >
            "Instead of getting lost in my chaotic async chains and dynamic
            imports, it treats my runtime execution paths as a first-class
            citizen to build a beautifully structured internal wiki."
          </p>

          <!-- Author Profile anchored at bottom -->
          <div class="flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-3 pt-2">
            <div
              class="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden bg-text-primary"
            >
              <img
                src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/javascript/F7DF1E"
                alt="JavaScript logo"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2">
              <span class="text-text-primary font-normal text-xs truncate"
                >JavaScript</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 6: PHP -->
      <div class="break-inside-avoid-column mb-6">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full p-6 bg-white border border-border/30 rounded-xl group min-h-fit"
        >
          <!-- Body Text (Top 75%) -->
          <p
            class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8 font-sans font-normal"
          >
            "Penqwin effortlessly bridges the gap between my legacy procedural
            routes and modern object-oriented patterns, keeping our internal
            guides completely intact during massive code modernization efforts."
          </p>

          <!-- Author Profile anchored at bottom -->
          <div class="flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-3 pt-2">
            <div
              class="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 rounded-sm overflow-hidden"
            >
              <img
                src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/php/777BB4"
                alt="PHP logo"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2">
              <span class="text-text-primary font-normal text-xs truncate"
                >PHP</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
